          <text x="170" y="325" text-anchor="middle" font-family="DM Sans,sans-serif" font-size="8" fill="rgba(216,242,232,.2)" letter-spacing="2.5">PRECISION QUARTZ</text>
        </svg>
      </div>

      <!-- Accessible explanations -->
      <div id="mtxt">
        <p class="ch-eyebrow">Chapter III — The Engine</p>
        <h2 class="ch-title">No Battery.<br>No Problem.</h2>
        <div class="hl"></div>
        <p class="ch-body">You don't need to know how watches work to appreciate this one. Here's what matters:</p>
        <div class="insights">
          <div class="insight">
            <div class="i-num">01</div>
            <div class="i-text">
              <strong>It never needs winding</strong>
              <span>The movement inside harvests energy from your wrist's natural motion. Wear it, and it stays alive.</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="insight">
            <div class="i-num">02</div>
            <div class="i-text">
              <strong>More accurate than you'd expect from wood</strong>
              <span>The Japanese quartz module keeps time to within ±15 seconds per month — that's precision you can trust daily.</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="insight">
            <div class="i-num">03</div>
            <div class="i-text">
              <strong>The stopwatch actually works</strong>
              <span>Those 3 subdials aren't decorative. Start, stop, and lap time with the two pushers on the side.</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="insight">
            <div class="i-num">04</div>
            <div class="i-text">
              <strong>Made in the same country that perfected precision</strong>
